main event: Observers in Corvallis, Oregon, witnessed an unidentified object moving overhead on 15 October 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 2 to 8 minutes,The object made a short turn to the south before continuing to the north,Various observers noted no sound, trail, or wind disturbance from the object,There were multiple witnesses, including a salesman and several university students,The case was labeled as having insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: A salesman and several university students.
